      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The threat of a severe storm prompted officials to suspend play last night in the Women's College World Series in Oklahoma City.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The threat of a severe storm prompted officials to suspend play last night in the Women's College World Series in Oklahoma City.</p>
        <p>U.C.L.A. led top-seeded Washington by 3-0 with one out in the fifth when play was stopped. Washington had the bases loaded. The game is scheduled to resume this morning and will be followed by a winner's bracket game between Oklahoma and Southern Mississippi, which was to be played late last night. Lindsey Klein hit a two-run homer in the third for U.C.L.A.</p>
